main event: A resident in Newington, N.J. reported observing an object with a white glowing rim and dark center rotating and emitting a high-pitched metallic sound on May 5, 1959.
interesting points: The object was described as having a white glowing rim and dark center,The object appeared to be rotating, accompanied by a high-pitched metallic whistling sound,The sighting direction was northeast to southwest,The report indicated the source's reliability as credible,The sighting characteristics were deemed distinct from known aircraft or other aerial objects.
